    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the design thing, but it feels like the model is being a bit dismissive of the actual cost of it all. at the end of the day, if you're taxing more people to fund these programs, you're taking money away from the very industries that create jobs. isn't it true that high levels of social spending and the taxes required to pay for them are a direct drag on economic competitiveness and private investment?",
